        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 3 at 8:32PM MST by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>Pacific moisture and an approaching weather system will bring
periods of light snow along the Northern Rocky Mountain Front
tonight into Tuesday morning. Sections of US highway 2 near Marias
Pass may see a wet 2 to 4 inch snowfall with some roadway
accumulation causing slippery driving conditions. Accumulations
near the East Glacier and Saint Mary areas will generally be less
than 2 inches.

Anyone with travel plans tonight into Tuesday morning should plan
for variable road conditions along the Northern Rocky Mountain
Front, including slippery roads and reduced visibility below one
mile. Slow down and allow extra time to reach your destination if
traveling.
</description>
